    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-03-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="565"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Sanford</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 413.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-03-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 12, 1867.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: What remains of the Belgian legion in Mexico
                    disembarked from the French transport Rhone on the 9th at Antwerp, in number 780
                    men. Of the remainder 200 were killed or disappeared, and the others have been
                    invalided or left behind. They were received in public barracks at Antwerp, and
                    those who need it are aided by the government to return to their homes.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with great respect, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>H. S. SANFORD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
